name: Europa Conference League
summary: In the Europa Conference League quarter-finals, Emiliano Martínez's penalty saves propelled Aston Villa into the semi-finals after a thrilling shootout with Fiorentina. The winners of this competition will automatically qualify for the 2024/25 Europa League. The draw for the Europa Conference League semi-finals will take place, with Aston Villa set to face Lille. The match between Lille and Aston Villa will be live-streamed worldwide. Several Premier League teams are still in contention to qualify for European competitions next season, including the Champions League, Europa League, and Conference League. Meanwhile, Fenerbahçe aims to reach the Conference League semi-finals against Olympiacos, while Disney+ has acquired the streaming rights for the Europa and Conference Leagues in Sweden and Denmark. In the Europa League, Leverkusen, Atalanta, and Roma advanced to the quarter-finals, while Liverpool, West Ham, and AC Milan were eliminated.

summary: The upcoming film "Abigail" is a horror thriller with mixed reviews. Some critics, such as The Los Angeles Times, describe it as a "fanged 'Home Alone'" with kidnapping elements, while others criticize its "silliness" and lack of darkness, as noted by Forbes. Variety calls it a "brutally monotonous genre mashup," but The Hollywood Reporter praises its "exuberantly over-the-top vampire horror-comedy." The Toronto Star sees it as a "heist movie that gleefully collides with a monster movie," while The New York Times labels it "horror by numbers." The Guardian finds it "fun-sucking," while Empire calls it a "wickedly enjoyable thrill ride." Flickering Myth notes that it has "all guts, no glory," and Collider summarizes it as "a vampire flick with lots of gore but lacking depth."

name: Jontay Porter
summary: Raptors center Jontay Porter has been banned for life from the NBA after an investigation into his gambling activities. The league concluded that Porter violated its rules by betting on the Raptors to lose a game, which is a violation of the league's conflict of interest policy. Porter has been removed from the Raptors' roster and will not be eligible to play in the NBA or any of its affiliated leagues. This marks the first lifetime ban for gambling by an NBA player since Tim Donaghy in 2007.

name: Smoking ban UK
summary: The United Kingdom has passed a landmark smoking ban that will phase out cigarette sales, making it the first country to implement such a generational ban. The ban targets individuals born after 2009, prohibiting them from purchasing tobacco products throughout their lives. The legislation aims to create a "smoke-free" generation and combat the health risks associated with smoking. This historic move has sparked both support and criticism, with supporters praising its potential to reduce smoking-related illnesses and opponents questioning its effectiveness and individual freedoms. The ban's implementation will be closely monitored, with potential implications for Canadian tourists visiting the UK and inspiring discussions about similar measures in other countries.
